<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="17.[812,1452,992,1240]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[812,910,993,1017]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[924,937,992,1016]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">â€“</emphasis>
This species has been adequately described and illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="Drew, R" box="[957,1162,1025,1048]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" pagination="567 - 654" refId="ref21269" refString="Drew, R. A. I., D. L. Hancock &amp; I. M. White, 1998. Revision of the tropical fruit flies (Diptera: Tephritidae: Dacinae) of South East Asia. II. Dacus Fabricius. Invertebrate Taxonomy, 12: 567 - 654." type="journal article" year="1998">Drew et al. (1998)</bibRefCitation>
. It is readily distinguished by the following characters: scutum black, postpronotal lobes black, notopleura yellow, anatergite black, katatergite mostly yellow, face fulvous with an inverted U-shaped black pattern, costal band overlapping R 
<subScript attach="left" box="[1101,1125,1165,1179]" fontSize="6" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">4+5</subScript>
, cells bc and c dark fuscous, femora and tibiae mostly black, abdominal terga mostly black. It is not a pest species.
</paragraph>
